# Spending & Inventory Tracker — Project Context

This project is a **Spending & Inventory Tracker** spreadsheet (**template version** in `CONFIG.TEMPLATE_VERSION`, year-based **YY.minor** e.g. **26.1**). `onOpen` runs `_maybeAutoUpgrade` when `tracker_script_version` (document property) differs — merges Settings types, patches Transactions, rebuilds Dashboard/Guide. Designed for **reusability** and **data migratability**. User patch steps: **APPLY_PATCH_V26.1.md**.

## Canonical contract (do not break)

- **Sheet names:** Exactly `Transactions`, `Dashboard`, `Settings`, `Guide`. Formulas and scripts depend on these; do not rename.
- **Transactions columns (fixed order):** A=Date … J=ID (formula); K=Up-front amount (Deposit / Pre-order paid); L=Linked deposit ID (optional, balance row). F=Total: if Type is Deposit or Pre-order paid then K; else Qty×Unit price. Types include Purchase, Income, Deposit, Pre-order paid; blank Type = Purchase. Inventory uses Purchase/blank only. Date validation; row 1 and column A frozen.
- **Settings:** Budget B2; currency E2 (label, e.g. USD); categories A from row 4; payment methods B from row 4; transaction types C from row 4. Used for dropdowns in Transactions.

## How it works

- **Transactions** is the single source of truth: each row feeds both spending (Total, Category, Date) and inventory (Item, Qty).
- **Dashboard** is formula-only: KPIs including Total Spent (all cash-out types), **Spending breakdown** (Purchases vs Deposits vs Prepaid), category/monthly trends (include Deposit + Pre-order paid), dynamic Inventory (Purchase/blank only).
- **Settings** holds budget, currency label, and dropdown lists. **Guide** sheet has short "How to use" text. All config in Settings for reuse.

## Tracker menu (all features)

- **Run setup** — creates/recreates all 4 sheets from scratch.
- **Apply fixes (keep data)** — merges missing default transaction types (Settings C); rebuilds Dashboard/Guide; patches Transactions; sets version marker.
- **Reset Transactions** — clears user data (A–E, G–I, K–L) but preserves Total (F) and ID (J) formulas.
- **Reset all** — full recreate with confirmation.
- **Export** — Transactions to sheet `Export_CSV` (tabular A–L, same as `Backup_Transactions`; avoids multiline cell corruption), Settings to `Export_Settings` (A–E values), full backup (`Backup_Transactions` + `Backup_Settings`). `exportTransactionsToCsv()` remains for string/file use. Import still falls back to legacy column-A CSV lines when the sheet is not tabular (newlines inside quoted fields can break that path).
- **Import** — Transactions import reapplies formulas + version marker; Settings import merges types + `_patchTransactions`; full backup also rebuilds Guide and sets marker.
- **Run tests** — `runAllTests()` checks sheets, headers, formulas, exports, imports, CSV parser.

